        -:   47: *           pivot row = j;
        -:   48: *       ELSE
        -:   49: *           pivot row = m;
        -:   50: * 
        -:   51: *   Note: If you absolutely want to use a given pivot order, then set u=0.0.
        -:   52: * 
        -:   53: * \param jcol The current column of L
        -:   54: * \param diagpivotthresh diagonal pivoting threshold
        -:   55: * \param[in,out] perm_r Row permutation (threshold pivoting)
        -:   56: * \param[in] iperm_c column permutation - used to finf diagonal of Pc*A*Pc'
        -:   57: * \param[out] pivrow  The pivot row
        -:   58: * \param glu Global LU data
        -:   59: * \return 0 if success, i > 0 if U(i,i) is exactly zero 
        -:   60: * 
        -:   61: */
